#MEM id=triple-pass-protocol source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/kai/skills/operating-system/triple-pass-protocol/SKILL.md
M|triple-pass-protocol|name: triple-pass-protocol
M|triple-pass-protocol|description: Kai's pre-delivery quality gate. Three passes — gen, Critique, Fix — before any analysis or report is delivered. Stark never sees the process, only the final output.
M|triple-pass-protocol|version: 1.0.0
M|triple-pass-protocol|Most anl errors happen in the interpretation step, not the data step. This protocol forces an adversarial self-rv before delivery — catching overconfident conclusions, misclassified signals, and missi
M|triple-pass-protocol|Produce the analysis, report, or insight in full. Don't self-censor during generation — write the complete output including all conclusions and recommendations.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stop. Become the skeptic. Ask every question on this list before proceeding:
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Signal quality:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is this a signal or is it noise? Does it meet the 3+ consecutive periods test?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- What is the base rate? Have I established the normal range before calling this an anomaly?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Am I presenting a range and confidence level, or a point estimate?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**ctx check:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is this anomaly account-specific, or could it be platform-wide? Did I WebSearch to check?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Have I tier-matched cp? Is this a fair gap for our current follower count?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is the benchmark I'm using current (< 90 days old) or stale?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**Interpretation quality:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Does the report end with "so what?" — a specific actionable implication?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Am I presenting data or interpretation? (Kai provides interpretation, not just tables)
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Have I named the confidence level explicitly: strong signal, early indicator, or insufficient data?
M|triple-pass-protocol|**vtr ctx:**
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Is this output scoped to the active vtr? No cross-contamination?
M|triple-pass-protocol|- Have I loaded the correct vtr baseline before interpreting the metric?
M|triple-pass-protocol|Address every issue found in Pass 2. Do not rationalize or skip. If the data doesn't support a conclusion, remove or downgrade the confidence level. If a benchmark is stale, flag it.
M|triple-pass-protocol|Stark sees the Pass 3 output only. Never narrate the triple-pass process.